              "type": "_accordion-row",
              "name": "t:names.accordion_dash_row",
              "settings": {
                "heading": "What handle material does the Mo Series use?",
                "content": "<p>The Mo Series features a deep burnt oak handle with a red G10 accent ring, hand-shaped for a comfortable, secure grip. Burnt oak is dense and moisture-resistant, so it won't crack or warp in humid conditions and gives you a steady grip whether your hands are dry or slick. The G10 accent ring is the same engineered laminate used on tactical and marine handles, so the bond between blade and handle stays sound under heavy use. Hidden tang construction.</p>",
                "open_by_default": false,
                "icon": "none",
                "width": 20
              },
              "blocks": {
                "text_qp8upf": {
                  "type": "text",
                  "name": "t:names.text",
                  "settings": {
                    "text": "<p>The Mo Series features a deep burnt oak handle with a red G10 accent ring, hand-shaped for a comfortable, secure grip. Burnt oak is dense and moisture-resistant, so it won't crack or warp in humid conditions and gives you a steady grip whether your hands are dry or slick. The G10 accent ring is the same engineered laminate used on tactical and marine handles, so the bond between blade and handle stays sound under heavy use. Hidden tang construction.</p>",
